Pupa (from detached exuvium, antennal exuvium still attached to adult, Figs 5-8 ). Able to discern distinct ocellar horns (Fig. 7 , och), a ventrolateral process (vlp2), and a bladder-like dorsolateral process on gaster (dlp2); see Heraty et al. (2015) for a full description of each structure. A dorsal mesoscutellar swelling could not be observed, but may be present. A darkly pigmented tergal bar on the basal terga (as found in
Schizaspidia
) was not observed on the exuvium; notably the corresponding tergal scar was also not found on the adult, so this structure is considered to be absent in this species.
